{"cursor":"847","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\nAn 'Arrow Security' is an instrument with a fixed payout of one unit in a\nspecified state and no payout in other states. It is a type of hypothetical\nasset used in the Arrow market structure model. In contrast to the Arrow-Debreu\nmarket structure model, an Arrow market is a market in which the individual\nagents engage in trading assets at every time period t. In an Arrow-Debreu\nmodel, trading occurs only once at the beginning of time. An Arrow Security is\nan asset traded in an Arrow market structure model which encompasses a complete\nmarket. Arrow Security is also called State Contingent Claim, Supershare Option.\n","linknr":103,"url":"Arrow_Security","recorded":1375082782,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Arrow_security&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Arrow_security&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Arrow_security","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=Arrow_Security&redirect=no","#mw-navigation","#p-search","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png","/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Economics","/wiki/Wikipedia:P","/wiki/File:Question_book-new.svg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png